### `Error: Hydration failed because the initial UI does not match what was rendered on the server`
**Cause**: Browser-only APIs (`window`, `localStorage`, `Date`, random values) used at render time
```typescript
// ❌ BROKEN — window is undefined on server
export default function Component() {
  const width = window.innerWidth  // crashes during SSR
}

// ✅ FIX — use useEffect for browser-only code
'use client'
import { useState, useEffect } from 'react'
export default function Component() {
  const [width, setWidth] = useState(0)
  useEffect(() => {
    setWidth(window.innerWidth)
  }, [])
  return <div>{width}px</div>
}
```

